Package: concordR
Title: Concordance-Aware Quality Control for Proteomic Interpretation
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Artur", "Shvetcov", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  email = "shvetsov1983@gmail.com")
Description: Translates an atlas of RNA-protein concordance across human
    tissues into a practical quality-control layer for proteomic studies.
    Given a gene list from a proteomics experiment, concordR tells you what
    you can and cannot conclude: which genes have reliable RNA-protein
    concordance, which are suppressed at the protein level despite high
    RNA, whether subcellular localisation is consistent with the measurement
    compartment, and whether enrichment results survive concordance
    correction. Built on an integrated atlas spanning 488,190 observations
    across 11,154 genes, 24 tissues, and 53 cell types.
